Data Pre-Processing

Upload

library(dplyr)
library(Seurat)
library(patchwork)
# Load the PBMC dataset
hdat <- readRDS(file = "../1_Input/snRNA_Human_ControlDissection_integrated_seurat_v2.rds")
# Create a feature that quantifies the number of mitochondrial counts (impurity)
hdat[["percent.mt"]] <- PercentageFeatureSet(hdat, pattern = "^MT-")
# Examine the feature-feature relationships, i.e. the relatinoship between ncount and nmito (a qualitative assessment of contamination)
plot1 <- FeatureScatter(hdat, feature1 = "nCount_RNA", feature2 = "percent.mt")
plot2 <- FeatureScatter(hdat, feature1 = "nCount_RNA", feature2 = "nFeature_RNA")
pdf(file = "../2_Output/FeatureCounts.pdf")
plot1 + plot2
dev.off()
## quartz_off_screen 
##                 2
plot1 + plot2

#
VlnPlot(hdat, features = c("nFeature_RNA", "nCount_RNA", "percent.mt"), ncol = 4)

# PDF
pdf(file = "../2_Output/VlnPlot.pdf")
VlnPlot(hdat, features = c("nFeature_RNA", "nCount_RNA", "percent.mt"), ncol = 4)
dev.off()
## quartz_off_screen 
##                 2

Normalize

# filter low-quality and/or over-represented features
hdat <- subset(hdat, subset = nFeature_RNA > 200 & nFeature_RNA < 2500 & percent.mt < 5)
# Normalize
hdat <- NormalizeData(hdat, normalization.method = "LogNormalize", scale.factor = 10000)

Highly-variable features

subset of features that exhibit high cell-to-cell variation

hdat <- FindVariableFeatures(hdat, selection.method = "vst", nfeatures = 2000)
# Identify the 10 most highly variable genes
top10 <- head(VariableFeatures(hdat), 10)
# plot variable features with and without labels
plot1 <- VariableFeaturePlot(hdat)
plot2 <- LabelPoints(plot = plot1, points = top10, repel = TRUE)
# Plot
pdf(file = "../2_Output/variableFeaturePlot")
plot1 + plot2
dev.off()
## quartz_off_screen 
##                 2

Linear Transformation (Scaling)

all.genes <- rownames(hdat)
hdat <- ScaleData(hdat, features = all.genes)

hdat <- RunPCA(hdat, features = VariableFeatures(object = hdat))
print(hdat[["pca"]], dims = 1:5, nfeatures = 5)
## PC_ 1 
## Positive:  MYH10, ITGA8, MYH11, LTBP1, PRKG1

## Positive:  F13A1, MS4A6A, RBPJ, MRC1, MS4A4E

non-linear dimensional reduction (UMAP/tSNE)

hdat <- RunUMAP(hdat, dims = 1:10)
DimPlot(hdat, reduction = "umap")

FeaturePlot(hdat, features = c("PKD1", "COL6A2", "PDLIM7", "FLNA",  "SMTN", # VSMC1
                               "MYH11", "ACTA2", "ITGA8", "PRKG1",  "CRISPLD1")) # VSMC2

# tSNE
hdat <- RunTSNE(hdat,dims.use = 1:20, reduction.use = "pca", dim_embed = 3)
DimPlot(hdat, reduction = "tsne", label = T)

Custom (Cell-Type) Annotation of Clusters

Once the clusters have been defined via unsupervised clustering, annotation of nuclei can be performed using established gene markers of vascular cell types.

library(ggplot2)

# Find all gene markers
Test<-FindAllMarkers(hdat)
write.csv(Test, "Gene_Markers.csv")
#Identify Clusters corresponding with known gene markers:
Fibroblast1_genes<-c("ABCA10", "C3", "ADGRD1", "FBLN1", "DCN")
